  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Central Sport has a reputation for its excellent service and cuisine. Benefitting from having a central location just a few minutes’ walk from the main street of <a data-udi="umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df}" title="Davos">Davos</a> and a minute’s walk from the ski bus stop.</p>
<h2>Alpine style</h2>
<p>The hotel has an inviting atmosphere - it's elegant, but has perfectly captured that cosy alpine feel we love when staying in the mountains. With nice social areas like the lobby and bar, you'll have plenty of space to catch up on the days activities over a drink with friends and family. Don't miss the tea and cake when you get back from the slopes. The bedrooms provide all the essential comforts, especially the Superior rooms which have been newly renovated. </p>
<h2>Excellent location</h2>
<p>Enjoy a great location in the centre of Davos Platz - just a few minutes’ walk from the main street and about a minute from the ski bus stop. The regular bus service, with links to the Jakobshorn or Parsenn lifts, Davos Dorf and Klosters, is free for local ski and accommodation pass holders. Making it really easy to get around and explore the <a data-udi="umb://document/f71942fdfeb0473ea01087403d83b724" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f71942fdfeb0473ea01087403d83b724}" title="Graubunden Ski Region">Graubunden Ski Region</a>.</p>
<h2>Relax and swim</h2>
<p>The Central Spa is the place to head for some rest and relaxation after big ski days. Ease the muscles with a swim in the heated pool or take a steam bath or sauna. It's all included in the holiday price. They also offer a range of massage treatments that are available to book and pay for locally. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
